      <TR VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT">
        <TD HEIGHT=141 COLSPAN=5>
        </TD>
        <TD VALIGN="TOP" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH=693 HEIGHT=133 COLSPAN=3>
                    
                      <div align="left">
                      <table border="0" width="696" height="136">
                        <tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#ffff80> 2000-06-23 - Gorden Updates</font> </td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19'></td></tr><tr><td width='686' height='19' valign='top' align='left'> <font face='Arial,sans-serif' SIZE=2 COLOR=#C0C0C0> <span class="newstext">Here are the latest Gorden Updates.
<ul>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/055851.html"><b>eBay</b></a><br>
    <i>[Quote from original post: sorry phelan but that is not good enough.
    Before everyone goes and flames this &quot;musk&quot; you need to know it is
    him. ANYONE at all with a FA could sell their account and try to MAKE it
    seem like it was this guy...hmmmmm would maybe cause people to try and bid
    more.]</i><br>
    <br>
    Very true, and its the same issue that we face daily. Weve already had
    several cases of people putting up auctions, making it appear to be someone
    on their server who they dont like, in an attempt to get them banned.<br>
    <br>
  </li>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/055820.html"><b>Does
    EQ Support Dual Processors?</b></a><br>
    Though EQ will run on a multiprocessor machine, any performance increase
    will be negligible. The application, though multithreaded, wasnt built
    specifically to take advantage of multiple processors.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/055872.html"><b>Jumping
    Into the Hole</b></a><br>
    <i>[Quote from original post: No one said not to levitate in... Read the
    patch message again it didnt say.]</i><br>
    <br>
    The patch message included:<br>
    <br>
    &quot;As a note, jumping in The Hole from Paineel is NO LONGER A SHORTCUT TO
    TOXXULIA FOREST. The GMs will not recover corpses for people who fall, or
    jump, or attempt to levitate into The Hole.&quot;<br>
    <br>
    I felt that this was as clear as I could make it without completely spelling
    it out. The risk of exploring new zones is quite high, and it should be. It
    really wouldnt be appropriate for us to describe in detail everything that
    can kill you.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/055457.html"><b>Rubricite
    &amp; Manastones</b></a><br>
    <i>[Quote from original post: I was wondering why Verant doesnt put rubicite
    back in the game? It is so rare now that the price is inflated too high for
    its worth.]</i><br>
    <br>
    Prices never inflate too high for its &quot;worth&quot;. The economy doesnt
    allow that to happen, as no one will pay more than it is &quot;worth&quot;
    to them. As for putting it back in, I suppose that its possible that it
    might make an appearance or two.<br>
    <br>
    The manastone, however, will not go back in. The manastone stopped dropping
    due to balance issues associated with it. Rubicite stopped dropping due to
    rampant camping.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/055891.html"><b>If
    I do &quot;this&quot; will I get in trouble?</b></a><br>
    It basically falls under fraud or harassment. Someone is bugging you for a
    port, you agree to port them, you port them someplace else. You do something
    other than what you agreed to do. Next thing you know the guy is dead, and
    lost experience due to something that another player did intentionally. Its
    basically the same as purposely training someone.<br>
    <br>
    Now if someone is harassing you with non-stop agressive begging, and refuses
    to leave you alone when you tell them to, please /report and /petition a GM.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/055923.html"><b>Experience
    Loss &amp; Death</b></a><br>
    Experience loss on death isnt calculated as a number of bubbles, but rather
    a numeric value. That value, is however, capped at the higher levels. In
    other words, a level 60 person will appear to lose less experience
    (comparing &quot;bubbles&quot;) than a level 55 person.<br>
    <br>
  <li><a href="http://boards.station.sony.com/everquest/Forum4/HTML/055928.html"><b>Manastones
    and The Hole</b></a><br>
    The Hole shouldnt be marked as a &quot;Kunark&quot; zone, so the manastone
    should work fine at the moment.</li>
</ul>
</span>
